definitions.definition: A river in north-west Queensland , Australia , which joins the Flinders River named after Lady Cloncurry in Ireland; in full, the Cloncurry River .
A town in the Shire of Cloncurry, Queensland , named after the river, on which it is situated.
A local government area in Queensland , Australia , with its administrative centre in the town; in full, the Shire of Cloncurry .
